Merck &amp; Co. removed Vioxx from use Thursday after new study results showed increased risk of heart attacks and stroke in people who used it for longer than 18 months.
articles released Wednesday by the New England Journal of Medicine say Vioxx may not be the only drug of its type that raises the heart and stroke risk.
Pfizer says there is no evidence that its drugs have problems similar to Vioxx because they are chemically different.
Patients on Vioxx for arthritis or other conditions should be getting letters from their doctors, although they can call them now.
